Wave 13.6.1 patch 0023 added per-IRQ-fire and per-pump-drain counters
that confirmed IRQ-1 is silently undelivered for ~42 s after main loop
entry on PODP 5V83 (real HW), then suddenly works at title-menu entry.
The architect's /tmp/wave-13-6-1-irq-mask-analysis.md identifies four
plausible causes (3a PIC mask, 3b chain wrapper, 3c memory-locking,
3d EFLAGS via setjmp/longjmp); the existing two counters cannot
discriminate between them. This patch adds the install-time and first-
IRQ-fire snapshots needed to discriminate 3a/3b/3c in a single CF iter.

Five new file-scope volatile uint32_t in SDL_dosevents.c, all
DOS_LockVariable'd because they are read from IRQ context via the
engine's phase-timing log:

  - doskutsu_kbd_pump_pass_count  bumped at top of DOSVESA_PumpEvents
                                  (one per flip on engine's main
                                  loop). Acts as monotonic ordering
                                  source for first_irq_ticks.

  - doskutsu_kbd_first_irq_ticks  set on first IRQ-1 entry to
                                  pump_pass_count + 1 (gate +1 ensures
                                  the 0-sentinel "never fired" stays
                                  unambiguous). One-shot.

  - doskutsu_kbd_irq_install_ticks pump_pass_count snapshot at end of
                                   DOSVESA_InitKeyboard. Always 0 in
                                   practice (no pumps yet) but logged
                                   for completeness so first_irq_ticks
                                   vs install_ticks compare is
                                   well-defined.

  - doskutsu_kbd_irq_vector_at_install  pm_offset of protected-mode
                                        IRQ-1 vector (int 0x09) read
                                        RIGHT AFTER DOS_HookInterrupt.
                                        Validates chain wrapper installed
                                        at expected address.

  - doskutsu_kbd_pic1_mask_at_install  inportb(0x21) snapshot at end of
                                       DOSVESA_InitKeyboard. Bit 1 (0x02)
                                       cleared = IRQ-1 unmasked at PIC.

Why pump_pass_count and not drain_count as the monotonic source: the
team-lead's spec-pass suggestion to reuse drain_count fails because at
first IRQ fire by construction nothing has yet been drained
(drain_count stays 0). pump_pass_count instead bumps once per
PumpEvents call regardless of keypress activity — gives a flip-
correlated ordering for free.

Why pic1_irr is omitted: the architect's §5b 5th field (PIC1 IRR
read via OCW3 0x0A → port 0x20) momentarily perturbs PIC state. Per
team-lead direction pic1_mask alone is enough to confirm/refute
hypothesis 3a; if 3a is refuted, IRR can land in a follow-up.

Default behaviour unchanged — no env vars, no behavioural changes;
this is a pure read-only diagnostic patch. Pairs with engine-side
patch 0070 which surfaces the new symbols in DEBUG.LOG.

See architect's /tmp/wave-13-6-1-irq-mask-analysis.md §5a for spec,
§5c for the discrimination table.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c | 80 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 80 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c
index 912da585b..b29e07c6d 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c
@@ -270,6 +270,49 @@ static int keyevents_tail = 0;
 volatile uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_irq_count = 0;
 volatile uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_drain_count = 0;
 
+/* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.2): IRQ-mask diagnostic snapshots
+   to discriminate hypotheses 3a/3b/3c from architect's
+   /tmp/wave-13-6-1-irq-mask-analysis.md §5a. Three install-time facts
+   plus one first-IRQ-fire ordinal:
+
+     - pump_pass_count: monotonic per-PumpEvents-call counter (bumped
+       at top of DOSVESA_PumpEvents below, regardless of keyboard
+       activity). Used as a flip-correlated ordering source for
+       first_irq_ticks. We can't reuse drain_count for this — drain
+       only ticks per byte pulled from the ringbuffer, and at first
+       IRQ fire by construction nothing has yet been drained, so
+       drain_count is necessarily 0 at that instant. pump_pass_count
+       is the cheapest counter that bumps once per flip without
+       needing engine cooperation.
+
+     - first_irq_ticks: 0 = handler never fired. On first IRQ-1 entry,
+       set to (pump_pass_count + 1). The +1 encoding ensures the
+       sentinel "0 = never fired" is unambiguous even if IRQ-1 fires
+       before any pump call (= pump_pass_count is 0 at that instant).
+       Engine subtracts 1 when interpreting; engine's log shows the
+       raw stored value.
+
+     - irq_install_ticks: pump_pass_count snapshot at end of
+       DOSVESA_InitKeyboard. Always 0 in practice (no pump calls have
+       happened yet at install time) but logged for completeness so
+       comparing first_irq_ticks vs install_ticks is well-defined.
+
+     - irq_vector_at_install: protected-mode IRQ-1 vector (.pm_offset)
+       read RIGHT AFTER DOS_HookInterrupt returns. Validates that the
+       chain wrapper installed at the expected address.
+
+     - pic1_mask_at_install: inportb(0x21) byte AT END of
+       DOSVESA_InitKeyboard. Bit 1 (0x02) cleared = IRQ-1 unmasked
+       (good); bit 1 set = IRQ-1 masked at the controller (bad).
+
+   All visible to engine via extern declarations in Renderer.cpp.
+   All DOS_LockVariable'd to allow safe IRQ-context reads. */
+volatile uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_pump_pass_count = 0;
+volatile uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_first_irq_ticks = 0;
+volatile uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_irq_install_ticks = 0;
+volatile uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_irq_vector_at_install = 0;
+volatile uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_pic1_mask_at_install = 0;
+
 void DOSVESA_PumpEvents(SDL_VideoDevice *device)
 {
     /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.3): the per-pump DOS_Yield() was
@@ -290,6 +333,12 @@ void DOSVESA_PumpEvents(SDL_VideoDevice *device)
         DOS_Yield();
     }
 
+    /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.2): per-pump tick. Bumped here
+       so the engine-side phase-timing log can correlate first_irq_ticks
+       against current pump_pass_count and localize when the first IRQ-1
+       fired in flip terms. ~1 pump per flip on the engine's main loop. */
+    doskutsu_kbd_pump_pass_count++;
+
     static bool is_extended = false;
     static int pause_sequence_remaining = 0;
 
@@ -390,6 +439,15 @@ static void KeyboardIRQHandler(void) // this is wrapped in a thing that handles
     /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): IRQ-fire counter for
        keyboard-regression bisect. Read by engine's phase-timing log. */
     doskutsu_kbd_irq_count++;
+    /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.2): record FIRST IRQ-1 fire
+       ordinal so DEBUG.LOG can show whether the handler ever ran and,
+       if so, roughly when in the run (in pump-pass terms ≈ flips).
+       One-shot: after the first non-zero write the gate stops further
+       writes. +1 encoding so the value 0 unambiguously means "never
+       fired" even if pump_pass_count is 0 at the moment of fire. */
+    if (doskutsu_kbd_first_irq_ticks == 0) {
+        doskutsu_kbd_first_irq_ticks = doskutsu_kbd_pump_pass_count + 1;
+    }
     keyevents_ringbuffer[keyevents_head] = inportb(KBD_DATA_PORT);
     keyevents_head = (keyevents_head + 1) & (SDL_arraysize(keyevents_ringbuffer) - 1);
     DOS_EndOfInterrupt(1);
@@ -408,8 +466,30 @@ void DOSVESA_InitKeyboard(SDL_VideoDevice *device)
     /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): IRQ-bisect counters. */
     DOS_LockVariable(doskutsu_kbd_irq_count);
     DOS_LockVariable(doskutsu_kbd_drain_count);
+    /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.2): IRQ-mask diagnostic
+       snapshots (see file-scope comment block above the variable
+       definitions for the rationale). All read from IRQ context, so
+       lock all of them. */
+    DOS_LockVariable(doskutsu_kbd_pump_pass_count);
+    DOS_LockVariable(doskutsu_kbd_first_irq_ticks);
+    DOS_LockVariable(doskutsu_kbd_irq_install_ticks);
+    DOS_LockVariable(doskutsu_kbd_irq_vector_at_install);
+    DOS_LockVariable(doskutsu_kbd_pic1_mask_at_install);
 
     DOS_HookInterrupt(1, KeyboardIRQHandler, &data->keyboard_interrupt_hook);
+
+    /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.2): post-hook install-time
+       snapshots for the IRQ-mask discrimination iter. Ordering of the
+       three reads is not load-bearing — DOS_HookInterrupt has just
+       returned with IRQ-1 unmasked at PIC1 and the protected-mode
+       vector for IRQ-1 (int 0x09) pointing at the chain wrapper. */
+    {
+        _go32_dpmi_seginfo info = { 0 };
+        _go32_dpmi_get_protected_mode_interrupt_vector(DOS_IRQToVector(1), &info);
+        doskutsu_kbd_irq_vector_at_install = (uint32_t)info.pm_offset;
+    }
+    doskutsu_kbd_pic1_mask_at_install = (uint32_t)inportb(PIC1_DATA);
+    doskutsu_kbd_irq_install_ticks = doskutsu_kbd_pump_pass_count;
 }
 
 void DOSVESA_QuitKeyboard(SDL_VideoDevice *device)
